cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about word embeddings, which are a key component of natural language processing (NLP) systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new compression method based on low-rank matrix decomposition with an added non-linearity, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses knowledge distillation, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also experiments with machine translation, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
